# terraform-aws-auth-cognito Workflow

## What this module is

Reusable Terraform module for Cognito user pools, triggers, and SES email config.
Consumed by `flo-core-services` `auth` leaves via `git::https://...?ref=main`.

## Pull requests to `main`

- **Never push directly to `main`.** Create a **feature branch**, open a **PR**.
- **Feature branch → `main` PRs do not require human approval.** Once CI (CodeRabbit) passes, merge immediately with `gh pr merge <n> --rebase`. Do not wait for the user.
- Only rebase merges are allowed (squash and merge-commit are disabled).

## HCL gotchas

- **No heredocs inside ternary conditionals.** Terraform does not support `condition ? <<-HEREDOC ... HEREDOC : fallback`. Extract the heredoc into its own `local` first.
- **No nested interpolations inside heredocs.** Extract sub-expressions into separate locals, then reference `${local.foo}` inside the heredoc.
- Module has **no `provider` block** — callers own provider config. Adding one causes "Duplicate provider configuration" errors in Terragrunt.

## Learnings protocol

Append an entry to `LEARNINGS.md` in this repo at the end of every session whenever a non-obvious discovery is made. Cross-repo learnings also go in `flo-docs/LEARNINGS.md`.
